%h2 Configure your site

- if Teambox.config.app_domain.starts_with? 'localhost'
  %div{ :style => 'background-color: rgb(255,255,230); padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(155,155,130); margin-bottom: 10px' }
    %p You haven't configured the correct domain name in <b>config/teambox.yml</b>. This will cause stylesheets not to work properly in production mode.

- if Teambox.config.smtp_settings[:domain] == 'domain.com'
  %div{ :style => 'background-color: rgb(255,255,230); padding: 10px; border: 1px solid rgb(155,155,130); margin-bottom: 10px' }
    %p You haven't configured outgoing email. You won't be able to create users without this working.

%p
  Now you have Teambox running. You'll now need to:

%ol
  %li Create a user account. This will be the administrator account.
  %li Create an organization. You can manage users and projects inside it.
  %li Brand your entry page. You can do this from your organization settings.

= link_to "Create your admin account now", signup_path
